rules.name: pre-oe-a-fronting
rules.notes: The fronting to ǣ is specific to West Saxon; Kentish and Anglian dialects had ē instead (Ringe 2014:149)

rules.name: oe-ae-retraction
rules.notes: Ringe 2014:199: The stressed ǣ existed only in West Saxon dialects at the time.

rules.name: oe-palatal-diphtongization
rules.notes: This sound change is specific to West Saxon dialects
